    • getTypelistValues

      public static TypeKeyData[] getTypelistValues(String typelistName) throws SOAPServerException, SOAPSenderException
      Given the name of a typelist, returns an array of all the typekey instances contained within. An exception is thrown if no typelist exists with the given name.
      Parameters:
      typelistName - the case-insensitive name of the typelist to look up. for example: "accidenttype"
      Returns:
      an array of codes of typekeys contained within the typelist
      Throws:
      PermissionException - if the caller does not have all of the following permissions: ADMIN
      SOAPServerException - if no typelist exists with the given name
      SOAPServerException - if the argument is null
      SOAPSenderException

    • getTypeKeysByAlias

      public static TypeKeyData[] getTypeKeysByAlias(String typelist, String namespace, String alias) throws SOAPServerException, SOAPSenderException
      For use during imports, returns a TypeKeyData instance corresponding to a typecode in the given typelist that matches the given namespace/alias. If no match is found, returns null. If more than one match is found, throws a SOAPServerException.
      Parameters:
      typelist - the name of the given typelist (case-insensitive)
      namespace - the given namespace (case-insensitive)
      alias - the given alias (case-insensitive)
      Returns:
      TypeKeyData instance corresponding to a typecode; null if no match found
      Throws:
      SOAPServerException - if more than one result is found for the given namespace/alias
      PermissionException - if the caller does not have all of the following permissions: ADMIN
      SOAPSenderException - if any argument is null

    • getTypeKeyByAlias

      public static TypeKeyData getTypeKeyByAlias(String typelist, String namespace, String alias) throws SOAPServerException, SOAPSenderException
      For use during imports, returns a TypeKeyData instance corresponding to a typecode in the given typelist that matches the given namespace/alias. If no match is found, returns null. If more than one match is found, throws a SOAPServerException.
      Parameters:

      namespace - the given namespace (case-insensitive)
      alias - the given alias (case-insensitive)
      Returns:
      TypeKeyData instance corresponding to a typecode; null if no match found
      Throws:

      PermissionException - if the caller does not have all of the following permissions: ADMIN
      SOAPSenderException - if any argument is null

    • getAliasesByInternalCode

      public static String[] getAliasesByInternalCode(String typelist, String namespace, String code) throws SOAPServerException, SOAPSenderException
      For use during exports, returns an array of strings representing external aliases to internal typecodes given a typelist, a namespace, and an internal code. If no aliases are found, then a zero-length, non-null array is returned. A namespace generally corresponds to an external integration source, but multiple namespaces per source are allowed. NOTE: this method allows multiple aliases to correspond to the same namespace-typecode tuple. If you require a namespace-typecode to resolve to a single alias, please use getAliasByInternalCode.
      Parameters:
      typelist - the name of the given typelist (case-insensitive)
      namespace - the given namespace (case-insensitive)
      code - the given typecode (case-insensitive)
      Returns:
      string array of aliases, or a zero-length, non-null string array if no aliases match
      Throws:
      SOAPServerException
      PermissionException - if the caller does not have all of the following permissions: ADMIN
      SOAPSenderException - if any argument is null

    • getAliasByInternalCode

      public static String getAliasByInternalCode(String typelist, String namespace, String code) throws SOAPServerException, SOAPSenderException
      For use during exports, returns a string corresponding to an alias to an internal typecode given a typelist, a namespace, and an internal code. If no match is found, returns null. If more than one match is found, throws a SOAPServerException.
      Parameters:
      typelist - the name of the given typelist (case-insensitive)
      namespace - the given namespace (case-insensitive)
      code - the given typecode (case-insensitive)
      Returns:
      string corresponding to a typecode; null if no match found
      Throws:
      SOAPServerException - if more than one result is found for the given namespace/typecode
      PermissionException - if the caller does not have all of the following permissions: ADMIN
      SOAPSenderException - if any argument is null
